/u/t-rexatron on TIL a week after Hurricane Katrina, after receiving little to no federal supplies, Sheriff Billy McGee stole 2 FEMA trucks full of ice from a U.S. military base to give to the citizens of Forrest County, MS.
My understanding is that National Guard troops can, but Army/Navy/Marines/AF, etc cannot be used to enforce the law/police communities on U.S soil, except in very specific circumstances. Source   